Gulliver Energy Ltd. (GLVR)  rallied the
most in more than three weeks after the oil and natural gas
company received a license to explore for minerals including
uranium at the Hatrurim site in the Negev.  The  shares advanced  7.3 percent, the most since March 11,
to 0.322 shekel at 11:21 a.m. in  Tel Aviv , giving the Ramat Gan,
Israel-based company a market value of 65 million shekels ($17.5
million).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shoshanna Solomon in Tel Aviv at 
